  <summary>4/4/2001--Introduced.
Expensing Technology Reform Act of 2001 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to permit the expensing of the cost of any qualified technological property (depreciable property that is qualified technological equipment, wireless telecommunications equipment, advanced services equipment, or network or network system equipment, and computer software).</summary>
